node.text:
If you’re unsuccessful, it’s mostly not your fault.

You’re held back by friends, family, and your bad environment…

Habits you got trained to have…

Thoughts you learned to have…

Actions you were taught to do...

And that’s keeping you from your dreams…

But good news: You can change that.

You don’t have to live with the hand you’re dealt with.

Most of the time, a small change can impact your life more than you ever thought it could.

For me, it was when I started my business on Amazon- that yanked me out of my old shitty behaviors and life.

If you wanna check it out,

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

...and they’ll show you how.

I wanted to create a better life…

Not just for myself but for my family.

My parents worked extremely hard every day and it was my dream to retire them.

I wanted to build a life with my then-girlfriend now-wife…

Running an online business isn’t always easy.

I failed over and over again…

But in the end I made it work.

And now I have an even bigger mission: To help millions of people to create a better life for themselves as well.

So, if you want to turn your life around…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity

node.text:
THIS is disgusting:

Promising outrageous numbers in short timeframes like that…

Let me tell you one thing:

It’s not how business works. 

Sure you could make a few bucks off his method, arbitrage works to get a little side income.

But you’re dependent on retailers to give discounts.

It’s not scalable, you have zero control and even if you would make a few grand this month, there’s no guarantee there will be anything to sell next month.

Plus, your competition will be insane because you literally have no way to stand out...

But I have no issue with his method since I also did arbitrage at first.

What I have a HUGE issue with is that he tells you, that you can make 100k like this until the year is over.

It won’t work and in the end, you’ll blame yourself for the failure and think that you suck.

You don’t.

You just didn’t know better.

Believe me, making 100k in sales is hard enough, launching the products, keeping stocks high, PPC, optimizing the listing and so much more…

And then, don’t forget the costs for it all.

In the end, after you made 100k in sales, you’ll probably keep less than 25k a year- you’d earn more waiting tables, so don’t leave your job for it just yet.

So the first step now shouldn’t be running to a retailer wasting your money on cheap garbage hoping anyone will buy it for full price.

Whenever you hear such a promise, the first thing to do is: Educating yourself.

Learn how online selling really works and then form your own opinion.

Here’s a way to get a good idea of how Amazon works:

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And you’ll understand why I’m so upset with his promise!

It doesn’t matter to you if they make trillions or not- it doesn’t affect your life one bit.

But if you’d be an Amazon seller on the other hand…

Every bit of growth ends up in your pocket as your own business grows with Amazon.

We live in a time that rewards those who help others win the most.

They make money by making you money- that’s their whole deal in a nutshell.

That’s why, the more opportunities they give, the bigger they grow.

What do Jeff Bezos, Elon Musk, Bill Gates and all other people have in common?

They all have 24 hours in a day.

So do you, so do I.

We all have an equal amount of time.

So how come that some of us are billionaires, and some not?

Well, it’s not about how much time we have, it’s how we use the time.

How focused are you on your goals?

How much of your time do you really use to work on your dreams?

Now that you remember what you really want to work on…

node.text:
It hurts me to see this…

People with amazing jobs and $300k a year salaries…

Lose everything the moment they lose their job.

Because the moment their salary is gone, so is their lifestyle and living standard.

Their success is tied to their job.

Working a job, buying a house and being happy forever worked 50 years ago.

But times have changed.

To make it in today’s world you need to make your money work for you.

In other words: invest.

If you are just starting out, it’s best to invest in yourself and your skills.

Want to start investing and break into a beginner friendly side-hustle?
